Session of 2025
HOUSE BILL No. 2261
By Committee on Transportation
Requested by Lieutenant Roy Wise on behalf of the Kansas Highway Patrol
2-4
1 AN ACT concerning the Kansas highway patrol; relating to the
2 employment classifications of Kansas highway patrol officers;
3 providing that Kansas highway patrol majors are to be within the
4 unclassified service and superintendents, assistant superintendents and
5 majors shall be returned with permanent status to the rank that such
6 officer held when the officer was appointed to such respective position;
7 amending K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-2113 and repealing the existing
8 section.
9
10 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
11 Section 1. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-2113 is hereby amended to read as
12 follows: 74-2113. (a) (1) There is hereby created a Kansas highway patrol.
13 The patrol shall consist of:
14 (A) A superintendent, who shall have the rank of colonel and who
15 shall have special training and qualifications for the position;
16 (B) an assistant superintendent, who shall have the rank of lieutenant
17 colonel; and
18 (C) officers and troopers who are appointed in accordance with
19 appropriation acts and as provided in this section.
20 (2) The superintendent and, assistant superintendent and majors shall
21 be within the unclassified service under the Kansas civil service act. The
22 assistant superintendent shall be appointed by the superintendent from
23 among the members of the patrol, and shall serve at the pleasure of the
24 superintendent. If a person appointed as superintendent, assistant
25 superintendent or major is a member of the patrol when appointed, the
26 person in each case, upon termination of the term as superintendent,
27 assistant superintendent or major, respectively, shall be returned to a rank
28 with permanent status not lower than the rank the person held when
29 appointed as superintendent, assistant superintendent or major. If the rank
30 is filled at that time, a temporary additional position shall be created in the
31 rank until a vacancy occurs in such rank. All other officers, troopers and
32 employees shall be within the classified service under the Kansas civil
33 service act.
34 (b) The superintendent of the patrol shall be appointed by the
35 governor, subject to confirmation by the senate as provided in K.S.A. 75-

