1 4315b, and amendments thereto, and shall receive an annual salary fixed
2 by the governor. Except as provided by K.S.A. 46-2601, and amendments
3 thereto, no person appointed as superintendent shall exercise any power,
4 duty or function as superintendent until confirmed by the senate. The
5 assistant superintendent shall receive an annual salary fixed by the
6 superintendent and approved by the governor.
7 (c) All other members of the patrol shall be appointed by the
8 superintendent in accordance with appropriation acts and with the Kansas
9 civil service act. No person shall be appointed as an officer of the patrol,
10 other than superintendent, unless the person has had at least five years of
11 service in the patrol as an officer or trooper. No person shall be appointed
12 as a trooper unless the person meets the following requirements:
13 (1) Is a citizen of the United States;
14 (2) is at least 21 years of age at the time of appointment;
15 (3) has not been convicted by any state or the federal government of a
16 crime which is a felony or its equivalent under the uniform code of
17 military justice;
18 (4) has been fingerprinted pursuant to K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 22-4713,
19 and amendments thereto, and a search of local, state and national
20 fingerprint files has been made to determine whether the applicant has a
21 criminal record;
22 (5) is the holder of a high school diploma or furnishes evidence of
23 successful completion of an examination indicating an equivalent
24 achievement; and
25 (6) is free of any physical or mental condition which might adversely
26 affect the applicant's performance of duties as a trooper and whose
27 physical health has been certified by an examining physician appointed by
28 the superintendent.
29 (d) No member of the patrol shall:
30 (1) Hold any other elective or appointive commission or office,
31 except:
32 (A) In the Kansas national guard or in the organized reserve of the
33 United States army, air force or navy.;
34 (B) in the governing body of a municipality:
35 (i) If the position to be held is appointed; or
36 (ii) if the position to be held is elected on a nonpartisan basis.
37 (C) On any appointed board, commission or task force which the
38 superintendent of the highway patrol deems necessary as part of the
39 member's or officer's duties.
40 (2) Accept any employment or compensation from any licensee of the
41 director of alcoholic beverage control of the department of revenue or
42 from any licensee of the Kansas racing commission or from any officer,
43 director, member or employee of any such licensee.

