1 (3) Accept any employment or compensation for services which
2 require the use of any state-owned equipment provided by the Kansas
3 highway patrol or the wearing of the patrol uniform.
4 (4) Accept any reward or gift pertaining to the performance of the
5 member's or officer's duties except with the written permission of the
6 superintendent.
7 (e) For the purposes of this section, the terms "governing body" and
8 "municipality" shall have the meanings ascribed to such terms in K.S.A.
9 12-105a, and amendments thereto.
10 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-2113 is hereby repealed.
11 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
12 publication in the statute book.

